The paper discusses the application of artificial intelligence and machine learning in wireless networking, specifically for 5G and beyond. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also extensively discusses the use of machine learning algorithms and their applications, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper covers topics related to optimization and management of wireless networks, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper also discusses the challenges and future directions of applying AI/ML to wireless networks, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
